HW5 notebook

Here is the first method for overlaying shape data on a raster.

Use the following packages (install them first), then use them via the library() call: tmap, tmaptools, rgdal, sp, OpenStreetMap, osmdata

These calls are useful: readOGR(), tmaptools::read_osm(), tm_shape(), tm_raster(), tm_dots()

  1. readOGR() your shapefile, store it in a var
  2. read_osm() the bbox of #1 above, store it in a var
  3. do tm_shape() on #2 + tm_raster() + tm_shape() on #1 + tm_dots() to specify point color and size
library(rgdal)
library(tmap)
library(tmaptools)
library(sp)
library(osmdata)
library(OpenStreetMap)
locations <- readOGR(dsn="C:/Users/ridhi/OneDrive/Documents/CS-585-DB/Ridhi_Shikha_HW5/mygeodata",layer="hw_five")
OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
Source: "C:\Users\ridhi\OneDrive\Documents\CS-585-DB\Ridhi_Shikha_HW5\mygeodata", layer: "hw_five"
with 9 features
It has 11 fields
location1 <- read_osm(locations)
tm_shape(location1)+tm_raster()+tm_shape(locations)+tm_dots(col = "red",size=1.5,shape = 16)

And heres the second.

Use these packages: PBSmapping, ggmap And these calls: importShapefile(), as.data.frame(), get_map(), ggmap(), geom_point()

  1. importShapefile() into a var
  2. convert it (#1 above) to a dataframe, store it in a var
  3. get_map() with a location thats in your collection of (lat,long), store it in a var
  4. do ggmap() on #3, + geom_point() on #2
library(PBSmapping)
library(ggmap)
loca <- importShapefile("C:/Users/ridhi/OneDrive/Documents/CS-585-DB/Ridhi_Shikha_HW5/mygeodata/hw_five.shp") 
dataf<- data.frame(loca)
point<- get_map(location = c(lon=-118.282833,lat=34.021853),zoom=15)
Map from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=34.021853,-118.282833&zoom=15&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=terrain&language=en-EN&sensor=false
ggmap(point)+geom_point(data=dataf,aes(X,Y),size=5,color="red")
